                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java:120-172                                                                                                 
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             120:    public Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> parseAllObjects() throws IOException                                                                                                      
                             121:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             122:        Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> allObjects = new HashMap<>();                                                                                                                
                             123:        try                                                                                                                                                                     
                             124:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             125:            Map<Integer, Long> objectNumbers = privateReadObjectOffsets();                                                                                                      
                             126:            // count the number of object numbers eliminating double entries                                                                                                    
                             127:            long numberOfObjNumbers = objectNumbers.values().stream().distinct().count();                                                                                       
                             128:            // the usage of the index should be restricted to cases where more than one                                                                                         
                             129:            // object use the same object number.                                                                                                                               
                             130:            // there are malformed pdfs in the wild which would lead to false results if                                                                                        
                             131:            // pdfbox always relies on the index if available. In most cases the object number                                                                                  
                             132:            // is sufficient to choose the correct object                                                                                                                       
                             133:            boolean indexNeeded = objectNumbers.size() > numberOfObjNumbers;                                                                                                    
                             134:            long currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                        
                             135:            if (firstObject > 0 && currentPosition < firstObject)                                                                                                               
                             136:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             137:                source.skip(firstObject - (int) currentPosition);                                                                                                               
                             138:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             139:            int index = 0;                                                                                                                                                      
                             140:            for (Entry<Integer, Long> entry : objectNumbers.entrySet())                                                                                                         
                             141:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             142:                COSObjectKey objectKey = getObjectKey(entry.getValue(), 0);                                                                                                     
                             143:                // skip object if the index doesn't match                                                                                                                       
                             144:                if (indexNeeded && objectKey.getStreamIndex() > -1                                                                                                              
                             145:                        && objectKey.getStreamIndex() != index)                                                                                                                 
                             146:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             147:                    index++;                                                                                                                                                    
                             148:                    continue;                                                                                                                                                   
                             149:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             150:                int finalPosition = firstObject + entry.getKey();                                                                                                               
                             151:                currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                         
                             152:                if (finalPosition > 0 && currentPosition < finalPosition)                                                                                                       
                             153:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             154:                    // jump to the offset of the object to be parsed                                                                                                            
                             155:                    source.skip(finalPosition - (int) currentPosition);                                                                                                         
                             156:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             157:                COSBase streamObject = parseDirObject();                                                                                                                        
                             158:                if (streamObject != null)                                                                                                                                       
                             159:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             160:                    streamObject.setDirect(false);                                                                                                                              
                             161:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             162:                allObjects.put(objectKey, streamObject);                                                                                                                        
                             163:                index++;                                                                                                                                                        
                             164:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             165:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             166:        finally                                                                                                                                                                 
                             167:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             168:            source.close();                                                                                                                                                     
                             169:            document = null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             170:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             171:        return allObjects;                                                                                                                                                      
                             172:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java:621-658                                                                                                             
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             621:    protected COSBase parseObjectStreamObject(long objstmObjNr, COSObjectKey key) throws IOException                                                                            
                             622:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             623:        Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> streamObjects = decompressedObjects.computeIfAbsent(objstmObjNr,                                                                             
                             624:                n -> new HashMap<>());                                                                                                                                          
                             625:        // did we already read the compressed object stream?                                                                                                                    
                             626:        COSBase objectStreamObject = streamObjects.remove(key);                                                                                                                 
                             627:        if (objectStreamObject != null)                                                                                                                                         
                             628:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             629:            return objectStreamObject;                                                                                                                                          
                             630:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             631:        final COSObjectKey objKey = getObjectKey(objstmObjNr, 0);                                                                                                               
                             632:        final COSBase objstmBaseObj = document.getObjectFromPool(objKey).getObject();                                                                                           
                             633:        if (objstmBaseObj instanceof COSStream)                                                                                                                                 
                             634:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             635:            try                                                                                                                                                                 
                             636:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             637:                PDFObjectStreamParser parser = new PDFObjectStreamParser((COSStream) objstmBaseObj,                                                                             
                             638:                        document);                                                                                                                                              
                             639:                Map<COSObjectKey, COSBase> allStreamObjects = parser.parseAllObjects();                                                                                         
                             640:                objectStreamObject = allStreamObjects.remove(key);                                                                                                              
                             641:                allStreamObjects.entrySet().stream()                                                                                                                            
                             642:                        .forEach(e -> streamObjects.putIfAbsent(e.getKey(), e.getValue()));                                                                                     
                             643:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             644:            catch (IOException ex)                                                                                                                                              
                             645:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             646:                if (isLenient)                                                                                                                                                  
                             647:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             648:                    LOG.error(() -> "object stream {} could not be parsed due to an exception" +                                                                                
                             649:                            objstmObjNr, ex);                                                                                                                                   
                             650:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             651:                else                                                                                                                                                            
                             652:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             653:                    throw ex;                                                                                                                                                   
                             654:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             655:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             656:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             657:        return objectStreamObject;                                                                                                                                              
                             658:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Introduce a safety cap on the `/N` entry (numberOfObjects) for object streams to prevent unbounded loops and O(N) overhead on malformed/fuzzed inputs:                           
                                a. Define a constant, e.g.                                                                                                                                                       
                                   `private static final int MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_ENTRIES = 2000;`                                                                                                                  
                                   in `PDFObjectStreamParser` (or in a shared parser-utils class), with the value tunable if needed.                                                                             
                                b. In `PDFObjectStreamParser` constructor (lines 5363), immediately after reading `numberOfObjects`, add:                                                                       
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   if (numberOfObjects > MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                            
                                       throw new IOException("Object stream has too many entries: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                          
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   This ensures any attempt to process a stream with an excessively large `/N` is aborted at parse-time rather than looping indefinitely.                                        
                             2. Mirror this cap at the call site in `COSParser.parseObjectStreamObject` to avoid constructing a heavy parser for a doomed stream:                                                
                                a. Before creating `PDFObjectStreamParser`, query the raw `COSStream`:                                                                                                           
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   int n = ((COSStream) objstmBaseObj).getInt(COSName.N);                                                                                                                        
                                   if (n > MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                                          
                                       if (isLenient) {                                                                                                                                                          
                                            // Skip this stream entirely                                                                                                                                         
                                            return null;                                                                                                                                                         
                                       } else {                                                                                                                                                                  
                                            throw new IOException("Object stream size too large: " + n);                                                                                                         
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                b. This check short-circuits any expensive parsing work on an oversized stream, triggering the existing lenient-mode fallback.                                                   
                             3. (Optional performance hardening) Optimize single-object parsing to avoid a full scan of `numberOfObjects` entries when only one object is needed:                                
                                a. In `PDFObjectStreamParser.privateReadObjectNumbers()` (the method that builds the `Map<Integer,Long>` of object offsets), modify its loop so that once the                    
                             requested object number is encountered, it can early-exit. This reduces cost on well-formed but large streams.                                                                      
                                b. This optimization is secondary to the cap logic and can be gated behind a feature flag or always-on for further DOS protection.                                               
                             4. Testing and Validation:                                                                                                                                                          
                                a. Add unit tests for object streams with `/N` just below, equal to, and just above the cap: confirm that streams below the threshold parse correctly, and those                 
                             above trigger an `IOException` or skip in lenient mode.                                                                                                                             
                                b. Re-run the existing PDFBox test suite (no tests should break) and the libFuzzer harness to verify that the timeout no longer occurs on malicious inputs.                      
                             5. Justification:                                                                                                                                                                   
                                 The primary hang stems from an unbounded loop driven by an attacker-controlled `/N` value. A cap prevents the O(N) work from growing arbitrarily large.                        
                                 Placing the check both in the constructor (defense-in-depth) and in the caller (`parseObjectStreamObject`) ensures early exit before expensive parser                          
                             instantiation.                                                                                                                                                                      
                                 Existing logic in `parseAllObjects` and lenient-mode handlers remains untouched; normal streams under the cap behave exactly as before.                                        
                                 This approach avoids tinkering with the fuzzer harness or test code and confines changes to the parser internals, preserving all existing functionality for                    
                             valid PDFs.                                                                                                                                                                         
                                 Potential side effect: very large but legitimate object streams (e.g., >2000 entries) now trigger an exception or skip. Mitigation: make                                       
                             `MAX_OBJECT_STREAM_ENTRIES` configurable or increase the threshold if required by downstream users.                                                                                 
                                 Similar pattern: PDFBox already enforces limits on recursion depth and file size; adding a bound on object-stream length is consistent with existing DOS                       
                             mitigations.                                                                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             - Initial issue: A libFuzzer run against the PDFBox codebase produced a timeout error.                                                                                              
                             - Patch attempt: Added bounds checks on the `/N` entry of PDF object streams in two classesPDFObjectStreamParser and COSParserto reject or abort processing when                  
                             the number of objects exceeds 2000.                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Result of patch: The libFuzzer harness still reports a timeout, indicating the patch did not prevent the fuzzer from hanging or taking too long.                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Fuzzer output: `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`                                                                                                                                     
                                - Context: The harness invokes PDF parsing paths that include object-stream parsing. The fuzzer run never completes within the allotted time, suggesting an                      
                             unbounded or excessively long loop or processing in object-stream handling.                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Observations from the Initial Issue                                                                                                                                              
                                - The timeout occurs before a crash or exception is reported.                                                                                                                    
                                - No stack trace or exception is shown; the process simply stalls or exceeds the time limit.                                                                                     
                                - The issue is triggered during parsing of malformed or specially crafted PDF streams (object streams).                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - File: `PDFObjectStreamParser.java`                                                                                                                                             
                                  * Inserted immediately after the check of the `/N` entry validity:                                                                                                             
                                    ```java                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    // Protect against maliciously large object streams to prevent timeouts                                                                                                      
                                    if (numberOfObjects > 2000)                                                                                                                                                  
                                    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                                        throw new IOException("Object stream has too many entries: " + numberOfObjects);                                                                                         
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    ```                                                                                                                                                                          
                                - File: `COSParser.java`, around line 634                                                                                                                                        
                                  * Added a similar guard when encountering an object stream in lenient or strict mode:                                                                                          
                                    ```java                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    // Check /N entry to avoid unbounded processing of large object streams                                                                                                      
                                    int n = ((COSStream) objstmBaseObj).getInt(COSName.N);                                                                                                                       
                                    if (n > 2000)                                                                                                                                                                
                                    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                                        if (isLenient)                                                                                                                                                           
                                        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                                            return null;                                                                                                                                                         
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                        else                                                                                                                                                                     
                                        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                                            throw new IOException("Object stream size too large: " + n);                                                                                                         
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    ```                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Patch Result                                                                                                                                                                     
                                - After recompiling with the two new if-statements, libFuzzer still hits the same `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                   
                                - No new exceptions or I/O errors are observed; the fuzzer run stalls in the same or a related code path.                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - PDFObjectStreamParser.parseAllObjects and its internal loops that read offsets and entries.                                                                                    
                                - COSParsers object stream delegation logic beyond the `/N` checkespecially code that invokes `parser.parseAllObjects()`.                                                      
                                - Any recursive or nested parsing calls that may not respect the new bounds checks (e.g., indirect object resolution).                                                           
                                - Buffering or I/O routines that read the raw stream datalarge buffers or skipping logic that may block.                                                                        
                                - The fuzzer harness entry point to confirm how timeouts are measured and whether the harness retries or loops.                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:

                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                                                                                             
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                                                                                                      
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             94:     * This will peek at the next byte.                                                                                                                                          
                             95:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             96:     * @return The next byte on the stream, leaving it as available to read.                                                                                                     
                             97:     *

                             115:     */

                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Overview and Root Cause Analysis                                                                                                                                                 
                                - The fuzzer timeout is caused not by the number of objects (/N) itself, but by unbounded or exceptionally large `FIRST` offsets (and subsequently object-stream                 
                             offsets) in malformed streams.                                                                                                                                                      
                                - PDFObjectStreamParsers logic uses InputStream.skip (or similar loops) to jump to the first object and to each object offset. If `FIRST` or any object offset                  
                             is extremely large or out-of-bounds relative to the actual byte-length of the stream, the parser will spin reading past EOF (or keep looping on skip), leading to a                 
                             hang and ultimately a libFuzzer timeout.                                                                                                                                          
                                - The previous patch correctly limited `/N` to 2000 entries, but did not prevent huge values of `/FIRST` or of the per-object offsets inside the stream header.                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Patching Strategy                                                                                                                                                                
                                A. Add bounds checks for the `/FIRST` entry in both PDFObjectStreamParser and in COSParser before delegating to PDFObjectStreamParser.                                           
                                   1. In PDFObjectStreamParser.java (immediately after reading FIRST):                                                                                                           
                                       Retrieve the streams declared raw length (COSName.LENGTH) or, if necessary, the filtered byte length (via `stream.getStream().getLength()` or                           
                             equivalent).                                                                                                                                                                        
                                       Enforce:                                                                                                                                                                 
                                           `FIRST` must be  0 and  declared stream length.                                                                                                                    
                                           Optionally, clamp to a reasonable absolute maximum (e.g. 10 MB) if no LENGTH entry is present.                                                                       
                                       On violation, throw `IOException("Illegal or out-of-bounds FIRST entry in object stream: " + firstObject)`.                                                              
                                   2. In COSParser.java (in the same block where `/N` is checked):                                                                                                               
                                       After `/N` guard, read `/FIRST` the same way.                                                                                                                            
                                       Perform the same bound check.                                                                                                                                            
                                       If lenient, return `null`; otherwise throw `IOException`.                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                B. Add bounds checks on each objectoffset read from the object stream header inside PDFObjectStreamParser.parseAllObjects.                                                      
                                   1. After parsing all `<objectNumber, offset>` pairs into an `offsets[]` array:                                                                                                
                                       For each `offsets[i]`: ensure `offsets[i]  0` and `offsets[i] + FIRST  declared stream length`.                                                                        
                                       If any offset fails, abort with `IOException("Illegal objectstream offset: " + offsets[i])`.                                                                            
                                   2. (Optional) Enforce that the offsets array is monotonically non-decreasing to guard against overlapping or out-oforder entries.                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                C. Preserve the existing `/N > 2000` rejection logic.                                                                                                                            
                                D. Do not alter any harness code, fuzzing flags, or test suites; all tests and existing functionality for well-formed PDFs should continue to pass unmodified.                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Detailed Steps to Implement                                                                                                                                                      
                                - Reopen `pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java`:                                                                                                                                 
                                   Locate the code block after                                                                                                                                                  
                                    ```java                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    firstObject = stream.getInt(COSName.FIRST);                                                                                                                                  
                                    ```                                                                                                                                                                          
                                   Insert:                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    ```java                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    // --- BEGIN BOUNDS CHECK ON FIRST ---                                                                                                                                       
                                    int declaredLength = stream.getInt(COSName.LENGTH);                                                                                                                          
                                    if (declaredLength < 0) {                                                                                                                                                    
                                        // fallback: if LENGTH entry absent or invalid, you may derive from filtered stream length                                                                               
                                        declaredLength = (int) stream.getUnfilteredStream().available();                                                                                                         
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    if (firstObject < 0 || firstObject > declaredLength) {                                                                                                                       
                                        throw new IOException(                                                                                                                                                   
                                            "Illegal or out-of-bounds FIRST entry in object stream: " + firstObject);                                                                                            
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    // --- END BOUNDS CHECK ON FIRST ---                                                                                                                                         
                                    ```                                                                                                                                                                          
                                   After parsing the header pairs into `int[] offsets`, loop:                                                                                                                   
                                    ```java                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    for (int off : offsets) {                                                                                                                                                    
                                        if (off < 0 || off + firstObject > declaredLength) {                                                                                                                     
                                            throw new IOException("Illegal object-stream offset: " + off);                                                                                                       
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    ```                                                                                                                                                                          
                                - Reopen `pdfparser/COSParser.java`, in the section handling object streams (around line 634 where `/N` is checked):                                                             
                                   Right after retrieving `/N` and applying the 2000-entry guard, add:                                                                                                          
                                    ```java                                                                                                                                                                      
                                    int first = ((COSStream) objstmBaseObj).getInt(COSName.FIRST);                                                                                                               
                                    int declaredLength = ((COSStream) objstmBaseObj).getInt(COSName.LENGTH);                                                                                                     
                                    if (declaredLength < 0) {                                                                                                                                                    
                                        // Optionally derive from the filtered stream                                                                                                                            
                                        declaredLength = input.getFilteredStreamLength((COSStream)objstmBaseObj);                                                                                                
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    if (first < 0 || first > declaredLength) {                                                                                                                                   
                                        if (isLenient) {                                                                                                                                                         
                                            return null;                                                                                                                                                         
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                        throw new IOException("Illegal or out-of-bounds FIRST entry in object stream: " + first);                                                                                
                                    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                                    ```                                                                                                                                                                          
                                - Rationale:                                                                                                                                                                     
                                   By rejecting object streams whose `FIRST` or individual object offsets exceed the actual byte length, we prevent unbounded skip loops in both                                
                             InputStream-based and RandomAccessRead-based skipping code.                                                                                                                         
                                   This aborts parsing early on malformed or malicious streams, ensuring that the fuzzer triggers an IOException immediately rather than hanging.                               
                                   All existing logic that handles wellformed streams (with valid `/N`, `/FIRST`, and offsets) is preserved.                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Justification and Side-Effect Mitigation                                                                                                                                         
                                - Correctness: Valid PDF object streams always have `FIRST  actual length` and offsets within `0..length-FIRST`, so no false positives on legitimate documents.                 
                                - Performance: The additional integer comparisons are negligible in cost.                                                                                                        
                                - Fuzzer Outcomes: libFuzzer will now see fast-reject `IOException` instead of a hang/timeout.                                                                                   
                                - No changes are made to fuzz harness, test code, or external libraries. All existing tests for PDF parsing remain green.                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. References and Similar Patterns                                                                                                                                                  
                                - The existing `/N` check in PDFObjectStreamParser and in COSParser served as a templatethis patch reuses the same throw/return pattern for `/FIRST`.                           
                                - The use of `COSName.LENGTH` parallels other parsers in PDFBox that guard against excessively large streams (e.g., image stream parsing).                                       
                                - No new dependencies or utility functions are introduced; all checks use existing methods on `COSStream`.                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===
