                             131:                        close();                                                                                                                                                
                             132:                        return null;                                                                                                                                            
                             133:                    }                                                                                                                                                           
                             134:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             135:                else                                                                                                                                                            
                             136:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             137:                    return parseCOSString();                                                                                                                                    
                             138:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             139:            case '[':                                                                                                                                                           
                             140:                // array                                                                                                                                                        
                             141:                try                                                                                                                                                             
                             142:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             143:                    return parseCOSArray();                                                                                                                                     
                             144:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             145:                catch (IOException exception)                                                                                                                                   
                             146:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             147:                    LOG.warn("Stop reading invalid array from content stream at offset {}",                                                                                     
                             148:                            source.getPosition());                                                                                                                              
                             149:                    close();                                                                                                                                                    
                             150:                    return null;                                                                                                                                                
                             151:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             152:            case '(':                                                                                                                                                           
                             153:                // string                                                                                                                                                       
                             154:                return parseCOSString();                                                                                                                                        
                             155:            case '/':                                                                                                                                                           
                             156:                // name                                                                                                                                                         
                             157:                return parseCOSName();                                                                                                                                          
                             158:            case 'n':                                                                                                                                                           
                             159:                // null                                                                                                                                                         
                             160:                String nullString = readString();                                                                                                                               
                             161:                if( nullString.equals( "null") )                                                                                                                                
                             162:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             163:                    return COSNull.NULL;                                                                                                                                        
                             164:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             165:                else                                                                                                                                                            
                             166:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             167:                    return Operator.getOperator(nullString);                                                                                                                    
                             168:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             169:            case 't':                                                                                                                                                           
                             170:            case 'f':                                                                                                                                                           
                             171:                String next = readString();                                                                                                                                     
                             172:                if( next.equals( "true" ) )                                                                                                                                     
                             173:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             174:                    return COSBoolean.TRUE;                                                                                                                                     
                             175:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             176:                else if( next.equals( "false" ) )                                                                                                                               
                             177:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             178:                    return COSBoolean.FALSE;                                                                                                                                    
                             179:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             180:                else                                                                                                                                                            
                             181:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             182:                    return Operator.getOperator(next);                                                                                                                          
                             183:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             184:            case '0':                                                                                                                                                           
                             185:            case '1':                                                                                                                                                           
                             186:            case '2':                                                                                                                                                           
                             187:            case '3':                                                                                                                                                           
                             188:            case '4':                                                                                                                                                           
                             189:            case '5':                                                                                                                                                           
                             190:            case '6':                                                                                                                                                           
                             191:            case '7':                                                                                                                                                           
                             192:            case '8':                                                                                                                                                           
                             193:            case '9':                                                                                                                                                           
                             194:            case '-':                                                                                                                                                           
                             195:            case '+':                                                                                                                                                           
                             196:            case '.':                                                                                                                                                           
                             197:                /* We will be filling buf with the rest of the number.  Only                                                                                                    
                             198:                 * allow 1 "." and "-" and "+" at start of number. */                                                                                                           
                             199:                StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();                                                                                                                        
                             200:                buf.append( c );                                                                                                                                                
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/test/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParserTest.java:49-57                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             49:        Map<Long, Integer> objectNumbers = objectStreamParser.readObjectNumbers();                                                                                               
                             50:        assertEquals(2, objectNumbers.size());                                                                                                                                   
                             51:        assertEquals(0, objectNumbers.get(4L));                                                                                                                                  
                             52:        assertEquals(5, objectNumbers.get(6L));                                                                                                                                  
                             53:        objectStreamParser = new PDFObjectStreamParser(stream, null);                                                                                                            
                             54:        assertEquals(COSBoolean.TRUE, objectStreamParser.parseObject(4));                                                                                                        
                             55:        objectStreamParser = new PDFObjectStreamParser(stream, null);                                                                                                            
                             56:        assertEquals(COSBoolean.FALSE, objectStreamParser.parseObject(6));                                                                                                       
                             57:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java:83-112                                                                                                  
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             83:    public COSBase parseObject(long objectNumber) throws IOException                                                                                                             
                             84:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             85:        COSBase streamObject = null;                                                                                                                                             
                             86:        try                                                                                                                                                                      
                             87:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             88:            Integer objectOffset = privateReadObjectNumbers().get(objectNumber);                                                                                                 
                             89:            if (objectOffset != null)                                                                                                                                            
                             90:            {                                                                                                                                                                    
                             91:                // jump to the offset of the first object                                                                                                                        
                             92:                long currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                                                                                                     
                             93:                if (firstObject > 0 && currentPosition < firstObject)                                                                                                            
                             94:                {                                                                                                                                                                
                             95:                    source.skip(firstObject - (int) currentPosition);                                                                                                            
                             96:                }                                                                                                                                                                
                             97:                // jump to the offset of the object to be parsed                                                                                                                 
                             98:                source.skip(objectOffset);                                                                                                                                       
                             99:                streamObject = parseDirObject();                                                                                                                                 
                             100:                if (streamObject != null)                                                                                                                                       
                             101:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             102:                    streamObject.setDirect(false);                                                                                                                              
                             103:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             104:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             105:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             106:        finally                                                                                                                                                                 
                             107:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             108:            source.close();                                                                                                                                                     
                             109:            document = null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             110:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             111:        return streamObject;                                                                                                                                                    
                             112:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java:113-118                                                                                                 
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             113:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             114:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             115:     * Parse all compressed objects. The stream is closed after parsing.                                                                                                        
                             116:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             117:     * @return a map containing all parsed objects using the object number as key                                                                                               
                             118:     * @throws IOException if there is an error while parsing the stream                                                                                                        
                             ```

                             ===Patch Result===                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The projects libFuzzer-based test harness is reporting a persistent timeout when exercising PDFObjectStreamParser. The attempted patch simply adds an overloaded                   
                             `parseObject(int)` method that casts its argument to a `long` and delegates to the existing `parseObject(long)` implementation. After applying the patch, the                       
                             fuzzer still times out, indicating no change in behavior.                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - The fuzzer run stalls and ultimately exits with:                                                                                                                                  
                               `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`                                                                                                                                                       
                             - No stack trace or exception was emittedonly a timeout marker from libFuzzer.                                                                                                     
                             - This indicates that a code path under test is taking too long or entering a non-terminating loop for certain generated inputs.                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Important observations                                                                                                                                                              
                             - The timeout arises within the PDF parsing code, specifically under the PDFObjectStreamParser logic.                                                                               
                             - The harness itself is only responsible for driving inputs into the parser and reporting a timeout; it is not the root cause.                                                      
                             - No crash or assertion failure is reportedonly a performance or hang condition.                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                             1. A new overload was introduced in `PDFObjectStreamParser.java` to accept an `int` argument:                                                                                       
                                ```diff                                                                                                                                                                          
                                --- a/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java                                                                                                
                                +++ b/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java                                                                                                
                                @@ -80,6 +80,10 @@                                                                                                                                                               
                                     * @return the parsed object or null if the object with the given number can't be found                                                                                      
                                     * @throws IOException if there is an error while parsing the stream                                                                                                         
                                     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                                +    public COSBase parseObject(int objectNumber) throws IOException                                                                                                             
                                +    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                                +        return parseObject((long) objectNumber);                                                                                                                                
                                +    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                                     public COSBase parseObject(long objectNumber) throws IOException                                                                                                            
                                     {                                                                                                                                                                           
                                         COSBase streamObject = null;                                                                                                                                            
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                             2. The intention appears to be to allow callers that hold object numbers as `int` to invoke the parser more conveniently.                                                           
                             3. After recompiling and re-running the fuzzer, the same timeout error is observed:                                                                                                 
                                `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for further investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                             - **PDFObjectStreamParser.parseObject(long)**: examine loops or recursive calls that locate objects in the stream. Look for conditions under which the method may                   
                             fail to advance or terminate.                                                                                                                                                       
                             - **Tokenization logic**: methods that read next tokens or skip whitespace, especially under malformed or extreme inputs generated by the fuzzer.                                   
                             - **Stream positioning and bounds checking**: verify that offset calculations and stream skips cannot become negative or exceed buffer limits, which could cause                    
                             infinite loops.                                                                                                                                                                     
                             - **COSBase and subclass implementations**: ensure that object creation or resolution does not trigger unbounded processing.                                                        
                             - **Input harness**: though not the root cause, review how the fuzzer supplies inputscheck for unusually large or repetitive buffers that might trigger                            
                             pathological behavior in parser code.                                                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:

                             ## Notes

                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Identify the hang                                                                                                                                                                
                                - The fuzzer timeout is caused by an infinite loop inside BaseParser.readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary(), which is invoked by parseCOSDictionary(...) when it                          
                             encounters invalid or truncated dictionaries. Because EOF (source.read() == 1) is never handled properly, or nested <<>> pairs are not balanced, the loop never                 
                             terminates on malformed input.                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Preservation of existing logic                                                                                                                                                   
                                - parseCOSDictionary(...) must still:                                                                                                                                            
                                   Read the opening << pair, collect name/value pairs, and on syntax errors call readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary() to skip ahead until either the next slash or                   
                             dictionary end.                                                                                                                                                                     
                                   On true from readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary(), give up and return the partiallybuilt COSDictionary.                                                                            
                                - Well-formed dictionaries (balanced <<>>) must continue to parse normally.                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary()                                                                                                                                              
                                Replace the current adhoc read until slash or > logic with a robust, depthcounting loop that:                                                                              
                                a. Tracks nested dictionary markers: start depth=1 for the initial <<.                                                                                                         
                                b. Reads one byte at a time, peeking ahead when seeing < or > to detect a true << or >>.                                                                                 
                                c. On <<, increments depth; on >>, decrements depth.                                                                                                                         
                                d. On EOF (read() returns 1), immediately returns true (unrecoverable, caller should abort).                                                                                    
                                e. When depth reaches zero, returns false (we have found the matching >> for the dictionary end).                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Detailed steps                                                                                                                                                                   
                                a. Open pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java and locate readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary().                                                               
                                b. Replace its body with the following pseudocode (adjusting to use source.read(), source.peek(), and the correct byte constants if necessary):                                  
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   private boolean readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary() throws IOException                                                                                                              
                                   {                                                                                                                                                                             
                                       // We have already read '<<', so initialize depth=1                                                                                                                       
                                       int depth = 1;                                                                                                                                                            
                                       while (depth > 0)                                                                                                                                                         
                                       {                                                                                                                                                                         
                                           int c = source.read();                                                                                                                                                
                                           if (c == -1)                                                                                                                                                          
                                           {                                                                                                                                                                     
                                               // EOF or truncated stream: cannot recover  abort                                                                                                                
                                               return true;                                                                                                                                                      
                                           }                                                                                                                                                                     
                                           if (c == '<' && source.peek() == '<')                                                                                                                                 
                                           {                                                                                                                                                                     
                                               // consume second '<'                                                                                                                                             
                                               source.read();                                                                                                                                                    
                                               depth++;                                                                                                                                                          
                                           }                                                                                                                                                                     
                                           else if (c == '>' && source.peek() == '>')                                                                                                                            
                                           {                                                                                                                                                                     
                                               // consume second '>'                                                                                                                                             
                                               source.read();                                                                                                                                                    
                                               depth--;                                                                                                                                                          
                                           }                                                                                                                                                                     
                                           // otherwise, keep scanning                                                                                                                                           
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                       // depth == 0  found matching '>>'; caller can continue parsing at this point                                                                                            
                                       return false;                                                                                                                                                             
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                c. Ensure that parseCOSDictionary(...) continues to call this method unchanged:                                                                                                  
                                   - On return true: abort and return the partial dictionary.                                                                                                                    
                                   - On return false: the parser is positioned just after the closing >>, so subsequent reads proceed normally.                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Regression and sideeffect mitigation                                                                                                                                            
                                - Well-formed PDFs: the new method behaves like the old one up to the first >>; name/value parsing and true objects remain intact.                                             
                                - Malformed/truncated inputs: the infinite-loop hang is prevented by explicit EOF detection and depth counting.                                                                  
                                - No changes are made to the harness, fuzzing logic, external libraries, or test code. Existing tests for dictionary parsing will still pass.                                    
                                - We are not removing functionality (we still skip invalid dictionary contents); we simply ensure the recovery code always terminates.                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Depth counting is a common pattern in PDF dictionary parsing (see similar logic in other parts of PDFBox for streams and arrays).                                              
                                - Explicit EOF handling prevents unbounded loops on malformed input.                                                                                                             
                                - This directly addresses the fuzzers timeout (infinite loop) without altering the public API or caller logic.                                                                  
                                - No broad exception swallowing is introduced, so we do not mask other errors.                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             <code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java:329-380</code_range>                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===
